    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="611"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d611">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11 G93/471.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">May, 14, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Ecuadorian Government, in a note received today from the Foreign Office,
                    offers to pay a lump sum of 280,000 sucres to cancel revolutionary bills: 86,000
                    cash; 14,000 draft at 90 on the Consul General, New York; and 50,000 monthly
                    until extinguished; deducting therefrom value of combustibles supplied by the
                    Government, and items objected to in account for damages. If railway company
                    refuses, Government of Ecuador reserves right to appeal to arbitration. Also
                    insists on review of the bills previous to revolution.</p>
                <p>Ecuador offers to pay 100,000 sucres without further delay and refer to
                    arbitration all points under discussion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
